# Command gh

## What does this command do:

GitHub CLI, or gh, is a command-line interface to GitHub for use in your terminal or your scripts.

## Installed from

For Fedora install using: `sudo dnf install gh`
For Raspberry Pi install using:
```
(type -p wget >/dev/null || (sudo apt update && sudo apt install wget -y)) \
  && sudo mkdir -p -m 755 /etc/apt/keyrings \
  && out=$(mktemp) && wget -nv -O"$out" https://cli.github.com/packages/githubcli-archive-keyring.gpg \
  && cat "$out" | sudo tee /etc/apt/keyrings/githubcli-archive-keyring.gpg > /dev/null \
  && sudo chmod go+r /etc/apt/keyrings/githubcli-archive-keyring.gpg \
  && sudo mkdir -p -m 755 /etc/apt/sources.list.d \
  && echo "deb [arch=$(dpkg --print-architecture) signed-by=/etc/apt/keyrings/githubcli-archive-keyring.gpg] https://cli.github.com/packages stable main" | sudo tee /etc/apt/sources.list.d/github-cli.list > /dev/null \
  && sudo apt update \
  && sudo apt install gh -y
```
For Mac install using: `brew install gh`

## Command path

For Fedora run: `/usr/bin/gh`
For Raspberry Pi run: `/usr/bin/gh`
For Mac run: `/usr/bin/gh`

## Command documentation

Docs can be found at https://cli.github.com/manual/

## Command options

### Flags
    --help      Show help for command
    --version   Show gh version

### Core commands
    gh auth <subcommand>        Authenticate gh and git with GitHub
      login                     Log in to GitHub
      logout                    Log out of GitHub
      status                    Show authentication status
      switch                    Switch active account
      token                     Print the auth token in use
      refresh                   Refresh stored authentication credentials
      setup-git                 Configure git to use gh as a credential helper

    gh browse                   Open repo, issue, PR, or more in the browser

    gh codespace <subcommand>   Connect to and manage codespaces
    gh gist <subcommand>        Manage gists (create, delete, clone, list, view, edit)

    gh issue <subcommand>       Manage issues
      create                    Create a new issue
      list                      List issues
      view <number>             View an issue
      close <number>            Close an issue
      edit <number>             Edit an issue
      comment <number>          Add a comment
      lock / pin / transfer      Lock, pin, or transfer an issue

    gh org <subcommand>         Manage organizations (list)

    gh pr <subcommand>          Manage pull requests
      create                    Create a pull request
      list                      List pull requests
      view [number]             View a pull request
      checkout <number>         Check out a pull request locally
      merge [number]            Merge a pull request
      review [number]           Add a review to a pull request
      diff [number]             View changes in a pull request
      checks [number]           Show CI status checks
      close / reopen            Close or reopen a pull request
      comment <number>          Add a comment
      edit [number]             Edit a pull request

    gh project <subcommand>     Work with GitHub Projects
    gh release <subcommand>     Manage releases (create, delete, download, upload, view)

    gh repo <subcommand>        Manage repositories
      clone <repo>              Clone a repository
      create                    Create a new repository
      fork [repo]               Fork a repository
      view [repo]               View repository info
      sync                      Sync a fork with its parent
      delete <repo>             Delete a repository

### GitHub Actions commands
    gh cache <subcommand>       Manage Actions caches (list, delete)
    gh run <subcommand>         View/manage workflow runs (list, view, cancel, rerun, download, watch)
    gh workflow <subcommand>    Manage workflows (enable, disable, run, list, view)

### Additional commands
    gh alias <subcommand>       Create/manage command shortcuts (set, delete, list, import)
    gh api <endpoint>           Make an authenticated GitHub API request
    gh config <subcommand>      Manage gh configuration (get, set, list, clear-cache)
    gh extension <subcommand>   Manage gh extensions (install, remove, search, upgrade, create)
    gh gpg-key <subcommand>     Manage GPG keys (add, delete, list)
    gh label <subcommand>       Manage labels (create, delete, edit, clone, list)
    gh ruleset <subcommand>     View repo rulesets (check, list, view)
    gh search <subcommand>      Search GitHub (code, issues, commits, prs, repos)
    gh secret <subcommand>      Manage secrets (set, delete, list)
    gh ssh-key <subcommand>     Manage SSH keys (add, delete, list)
    gh status                   Show relevant issues, PRs, and notifications
    gh variable <subcommand>    Manage Actions variables (set, get, delete, list)

### Useful environment variables
    GH_HOST                     Override the default GitHub host
    GITHUB_TOKEN / GH_TOKEN     Token for authentication
    GH_ENTERPRISE_TOKEN         Token for GitHub Enterprise

### Examples
# Authenticate
gh auth login

# Clone a repo
gh repo clone owner/repo

# Create a PR from the current branch
gh pr create --title "My feature" --body "Description"

# View open PRs
gh pr list

# Check out PR #42
gh pr checkout 42

# Create an issue
gh issue create --title "Bug report" --body "Details here"

# View CI checks on current PR
gh pr checks

# Open current repo in browser
gh browse

# Make a raw API call
gh api repos/owner/repo/issues
